         If they're going to check to see if player x already cast a dot on mob y,... then there has to be a seperate identifier for that player's cast of that dot. Which means, that there has to be a seperate buff slot occupied for every caster, for every instance of every dot. </P><P>Regardless, unless every person that's going to cast a dot lands the dot in the same tick, then there's no way to track the time remaining for each caster's instance of the dot to act in. Which means again, there has to be a seperate identifier for every dot cast by every caster. </P><P>And on top of that, every cast of every dot builds hate and assigns "credit" to the person who's done the damage of that dot. To track hate of every caster, and to tally xp, there has to be a seperate identifier for every dot from every caster.</P><P>Removing extended affliction doesn't solve these issues.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
